cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the semantic labeling of LiDAR point clouds using deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The focus on network architecture and portability suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) angle, while the use of LiDAR data and semantic labeling suggests a natural language processing (NLP) angle (cs.CL). Finally, the paper does not deal with specific LiDAR hardware or sensor design, so it is less likely to belong to the cs.AR or cs.ROBOTS sub-categories.
